The paper deals with a geometric packing problem involving squares in the unit square, which suggests that it belongs to the computational geometry (cs.CG) sub-category. The algorithmic aspects of computing the region $R(S)$ and the NP-completeness result suggest that it may also belong to the data structures (cs.DS), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), computational complexity (cs.CC), and game theory (cs.GT) sub-categories.
